&lt;p&gt;Band 6 Specialist Public Health Nurse for Children in Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Secondment or Fixed Term contract for 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 clinician to join our Children in Care team in Bradford for 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work as part of the District wide health team who deliver the statutory health assessment service and work to promote strategies to improve health outcomes for Children in Care. Enabling and empowering young people to be involved in the assessment of their health needs and the delivery of their health plan is a key element of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Specialist Public Health Nurse who displays high personal levels of competence, judgment, integrity and personal accountability who will advocate for the children and young people in their care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will have experience of working within Children’s Services and will have a minimum of 1 years SCPHN experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to have clinical knowledge around Children in Care, including relevant safeguarding knowledge. They should use a trauma informed approach to care and understand how ACEs impact children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date 22nd November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short Listing Date 23rd November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date 30th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
